This paper deals with the efficient evaluation of potential fields in biomolecular hydrodynamics simulations, which involves numerical methods for solving partial differential equations. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science (cs.CE) sub-category. Additionally, the paper involves the use of fast multipole methods, which are commonly used in numerical analysis and scientific computing, suggesting that the paper could also belong to the Mathematical Software (cs.MS) sub-category. Other possible sub-categories include Numerical Analysis (cs.NA), Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC), and Soft Condensed Matter (cs.SC), as the paper deals with parallel computing, adaptive fast multipole methods, and the hydrodynamics of biomolecular systems.
